  <entry>
    <id>tag:github.com,2008:Grit::Commit/b64fd5db2526b33b5da6b8182f50bba8042b82af</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/commit/b64fd5db2526b33b5da6b8182f50bba8042b82af"/>
    <title>
        Respect min and max when building ticks (#4860)
    </title>
    <updated>2017-10-20T07:03:38Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/322311?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>benmccann</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/benmccann</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;Respect min and max when building ticks (#4860)

Generate time scale ticks (`ticks.source: &amp;#39;auto&amp;#39;`) based on the effective visualized range instead of the actual data range, meaning that the computed units and/or step size may change if the time options min and max are different from the data min and max.&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
