    <id>tag:github.com,2008:Grit::Commit/3fe198c86098ae50d5d5e9b74d111d5f8fa74bf0</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/commit/3fe198c86098ae50d5d5e9b74d111d5f8fa74bf0"/>
    <title>
        Fix responsive issue when the chart is recreated (#4774)
    </title>
    <updated>2017-10-07T15:43:09Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/3874900?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>simonbrunel</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/simonbrunel</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;Fix responsive issue when the chart is recreated (#4774)

Chrome specific issue that happens when destroying a chart and re-creating it immediately (same animation frame?). The CSS animation used to detect when the canvas become visible is not re-evaluated, breaking responsiveness. Accessing the `offsetParent` property will force a reflow and re-evaluate the CSS animation.&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
